From my lab:
Cisco IOS XE Software, Version 16.12.03
cisco CSR1000V

GET: https://192.168.122.89/restconf/data/ietf-interfaces:interfaces/interface=Loopback0

Output:
{
 "ietf-interfaces:interface": {
 "name": "Loopback0",
 "type": "iana-if-type:softwareLoopback",
 "enabled": true,
 "ietf-ip:ipv4": {
 "address": [
 {
 "ip": "1.2.3.4",
 "netmask": "255.255.255.0"
 }
 ]
 },
 "ietf-ip:ipv6": {}
 }
}
 bboycoi is right about the uri. Though the output shows "ietf-interfaces:interface" the request has "ietf-interfaces:interfaces" (with "s"). If removed, wont work. Neither would work with "/" instead of "=" in the request (as offered in option "A").
